body:
> The only difference is in how you use configs that are bundled with the plugin. 

@nzakas could you provide a bit more info on how to use configs that are bundled with the plugin in the new (flat) config? 

then, i'll add the update to the docs

It would look like this:

```js
import jsdoc from "eslint-plugin-jsdoc";

export default [
    // replacement for extends -- just drop the object right into the array
    jsdoc.configs.recommended,
    {
        files: ["**/*.js"],
        plugins: {
            jsdoc: jsdoc
        }
        rules: {
            "jsdoc/require-description": "error",
            "jsdoc/check-values": "error"
        }  
    }
];
```
